de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.administrative

Class AdministrativeFusion

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.administrative.AdministrativeFusion

  • public class AdministrativeFusion
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is responsible for fusing administrative metadata. Therefore the metadata information corresponding to every URI are added by calling add(ParsedMetadata). This method is also responsible for the actual fusion in this case. After all metadata information is added the fuse() is called. It creates the necessary properties and adds them the the scopeResource.
    Since:
    25.03.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add(ParsedMetadata singleMetadata)
        This method does the actual fusion work. It tries to obtain the license name of the given ParsedMetadata object by calling #getLicenseName(URI) and tries to load the properties file named by the licenseName from the licenses folder. Finally the field overallLicenseDescription is updated with the obtained LicenseDescription object.
        Parameters:
        singleMetadata - - a ParsedMetadata object which contains the license URI.

      • fuse

        public void fuse()
        This method creates the different Property objects by calling the specific method. These properties are added to the scopeResource. This method doesn't actual fuses the objects since the fusion takes place while adding them to the object.
